These three views aren't built yet — they're mockups, designed from the foundation. They show what the platform's intelligence will surface about the evidence layer itself. A status view — where evidence is provided, pending, or flagged as gap, distributed across Business Units. A freshness timeline — what's expired, what's expiring this cycle, what's coming up, so the Risk team plans ahead instead of reacting. An applicability view — how controls reach across the application portfolio, and which controls carry the broadest accountability. Same source, same refresh cadence. Intelligence the Risk team gets without writing a query.
